 familiar material, the book is essential reading for specialist, undergraduate and postgraduate researchers working on medieval performance, gender and queer studies, Jewish-Christian studies and time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntisemitism in literature. 0aBible playsxHistory and criticism. 0aChristian drama, English (Middle)xHistory and criticism. 0aSex in literature. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2020. 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aDRAMA / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChristian.  aJew.  aanti-Semitism.  adrama.  agender.  alay.  amedieval.  aperformance.  aqueer.  atime.1 aBlack, Daisy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614687840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526146878423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526146878/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles